  "text": "Here we set up the problem under the general distribution f (r) and discuss results and intuition from the general model. We describe the set of equilibria in pure strategies in Appendix 2. [CITATION_1] One might also posit a competitive click fraud cost function c(z; r), where dc dr < 0; to allow for the probability of competitive click fraud detection to fall with in ‡ationary click fraud. We expect the two types of click fraud can be independently detected, given that website owners' fraudulent clicks will come exclusively from their own sites, while competitive click fraud is more likely to occur on search engines'main pages. The results presented below are virtually unchanged under the assumption that c(z) = c(z; r).",
